import { useState, useEffect} from 'react' import './App.css' import axios from 'axios' const App = () => { useEffect(() => { console.log('effect') axios .get('http://localhost:3001/notes') .then(response => { console.log('promise fulfilled') console.log(response.data) setNotes(response.data) }) }, []) const [notes, setNotes] = useState([ { serialNumber:'', snapshotTimestamp:'', closestDistance: 0, owner: '', ownerEmail: '' , phone:''} ]) const showNotes = notes.map(note=> {return(

Owner: {note.owner}
Phone: {note.phone}
Email: {note.ownerEmail}
serialNumber: {note.serialNumber}
Last time: {note.snapshotTimestamp}
closestDistance: {note.closestDistance}

)}) return (

Phonebook

{showNotes}

) } export default App
